      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Build the masala base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the {{vegetable-oil}} in a wide pan over medium heat. Fry the {{onion}} for 5 minutes. Add the {{garlic}} and {{ginger-root}} and cook for 1 minute. Add the {{garam-masala}}, {{smoked-paprika}}, {{cumin-ground}}, {{coriander-ground}}, {{chilli-powder}}, and {{tomato-puree}} and cook for 1 minute until fragrant. Transfer to the slow cooker. Add the {{chicken-thighs-boneless}}, {{tinned-tomatoes}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Cook on low for 6 hours, until the chicken is tender. Stir in the {{double-cream}} and taste. Adjust seasoning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Increase the smoked paprika to 3 teaspoons and the tomato puree to 3 tablespoons. The red colour comes from the combination of the two",
              "cause": "Not enough smoked paprika or tomato puree",
              "symptom": "Colour pale orange rather than deep red"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Stir in the double cream at the end. It rounds the acidity from the tomatoes and gives the sauce its characteristic body",
              "cause": "Cream not added or too little",
              "symptom": "Sauce thin and sharp"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Start with 0.25 teaspoon and taste. The spice builds over 6 hours. Add more at the end if needed",
              "cause": "UK chilli powder is pure chilli, much hotter than the US blend",
              "symptom": "Spice level too strong after cooking"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chicken tikka masala is cooked more in British homes than any other curry. The slow cooker version produces a sauce that is richer than a 20-minute weeknight version because the tomatoes reduce and concentrate over six hours. Serve with basmati rice, naan, and a cucumber raita to cut through the richness.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
